│ The crash is an assertion failure: `isValidOperands(V1, V2, Mask) && "Invalid shuffle vector instruction operands!"` inside the `ShuffleVectorInst` constructor. This means the SLP      │
│ vectorizer is attempting to create a `shufflevector` instruction with incompatible vector operands (e.g., different types or different numbers of elements).                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The stack trace points to `llvm::slpvectorizer::BoUpSLP::gather`, which is called during the process of vectorizing a group of instructions, specifically originating from               │
│ `vectorizeStoreChain`. This tells me the vectorizer is trying to gather scalar values to form a vector that will be stored.                                                              │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
